A 55-year old pastor, Rufus Oyediran, has been ordered to be remanded at the correctional centre in Ado-Ekiti, Ekiti State over alleged rape of a 13-year-old girl in Efon-Alaye. A magistrate, Mr. Bankole Oluwasanmi, ordered that the defendant be remanded in prison custody until the case came up for hearing. The police prosecutor, Inspector Oriyomi Akinwale, told the court that the defendant committed the offence of rape on a 13-year-old minor. He said the offence is punishable under Section 31 of Child Right Laws of Ekiti State 2012. The police said the victim was passing through the house of the man when he called her. He said the man undressed and had sexual intercourse with her. The prosecutor said the victim’s twin sister saw her coming from the suspect’s house and reported to their grandmother who they lived with. The case was adjourned to April 19, for hearing. 